<div class="article__date font--sans text--xs gray--dark">
<span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2017-10-17T12:00:26-05:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime">Oct 17, 2017</span> <div class="js-readtime dn space-half--top"><em>19 minute read</em></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="spacing">
<div class="article__hgroup">
<a href="/2356366/horror-vault" class="cluster-link upper space-half--btm dib font--sans text--s ls--2" data-ga-event-category="cluster-eyebrow" data-ga-event-on="click" data-ga-event-action="click" data-ga-event-label="/2356366/horror-vault" data-amplitude-internal-source="cluster eyebrow"><strong>The Horror Vault</strong></a> <h1 class="article__title heading__one heading__one--xl">Inside the Mind of Thru-Hiking&#039;s Most Devious Con Man</h1>
</div>
<h2 class="article__subtitle font--secondary">For more than two decades, Jeff Caldwell has lured in hikers, couchsurfers, and other women (and they're almost always women), enthralling them with his tales of adventure. Then he manufactures personal crises and exploits their sympathy to rip them off. Our writer corresponded with Caldwell while he was still on the run, and came away with an intimate look at the life of a serial scammer who's found his easy marks in the outdoor community. </h2>
</div>
<div class="article__body-wrap">
<div class="article__body article__body--longform post-entry spacing js-article-body has-dropcap">
